== 典礼资讯 ==
[[File:Billy_Crystal_VF_2012_Shankbone.JPG|thumb]]
由于[[第75届奥斯卡金像奖|去年颁奖典礼]]的收视率很不理想，电影艺术与科学学院于是寻求作出多项调整，并为即将上演的新一届颁奖典礼聘请新[[制片人|制片人]]。学院宣布本届晚会将于二月底举行，而不是往年的三月底或四月初<ref>{{cite news |title=Save the date: Next year's Oscars move to February |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2003-03-27/news/0303280034_1_oscar-ballots-spirit-awards-golden-globes |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=Chicago Tribune |publisher=Tribune Company |date=2003-03-27 |archive-date=2013-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011111343/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2003-03-27/news/0303280034_1_oscar-ballots-spirit-awards-golden-globes |dead-url=no }}</ref>。艺术与科学学院通讯主任约翰·帕夫利克（{{lang|en|John Pavlik}}）称，将典礼提前一个月是为了“巩固颁奖典礼下滑的收视率并保护奥斯卡作为全国超群绝伦颁奖活动的地位”<ref>{{cite news |last=Lyman |first=Rick |title=Oscars to Arrive A Month Earlier Starting in 2004 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2002/08/05/movies/oscars-to-arrive-a-month-earlier-starting-in-2004.html |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=The New York Times |publisher=The New York Times Company |date=2002-08-05 |quote=to bolster the ceremony's sagging television ratings and protect the Oscar's status as the nation's pre-eminent awards event. |archive-date=2013-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011111726/http://www.nytimes.com/2002/08/05/movies/oscars-to-arrive-a-month-earlier-starting-in-2004.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。虽然学院的多位人员都否认了这一原因，一些业内人士推测，颁奖日期的提前也是为了减轻电影制片公司在奥斯卡季节里激烈的宣传和游说活动<ref>{{cite news|title=Decisison 2004 |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/newsweek/2003/03/12/decision-2004.html |accessdate=2013-07-19 |work=Newsweek |publisher=The Daily Beast |date=2003-03-12 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130719204006/http://www.thedailybeast.com/newsweek/2003/03/12/decision-2004.html |archivedate=2013-07-19 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。这也是继[[第14届奥斯卡金像奖|第14届]]以来，首次没有在3-4月份举行的颁奖典礼<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheehan |first=Paul |title=Live Blog: The 83rd Annual Academy Awards |url=http://www.goldderby.com/news/1222/live-blog-the-83rd-annual-academy-awards.html |work=''Gold Derby'' |accessdate=2013-10-11 |date=2011-02-27 |archive-date=2014-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222184339/http://www.goldderby.com/news/1222/live-blog-the-83rd-annual-academy-awards.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2003年8月，电影制片人乔·罗斯获聘监管颁奖典礼的制作，他于次月请来老牌奥斯卡主持人比利·克里斯托第8次主持颁奖典礼<ref>{{cite news |last=Grossberg |first=Josh |title=Oscar Brings Back Billy Crystal |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/45908/oscar-brings-back-billy-crystal |accessdate=2013-10-16 |work=E! |publisher=NBCUniversal |date=2003-09-24 |archive-date=2013-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011121811/http://www.eonline.com/news/45908/oscar-brings-back-billy-crystal |dead-url=no }}</ref>。为了给节目做宣传，罗斯制作了三段预告片，每段都使用了不同的流行曲段，分别是[[麥當娜|麥當娜]]的“{{lang|en|Hollywood}}”，{{lang|en|[[OutKast|OutKast]]}}的“{{lang|en|[[Hey_Ya!|Hey Ya!]]}}”以及[[粉红佳人|粉红佳人]]的“{{lang|en|[[Get_the_Party_Started|Get the Party Started]]}}”。预告片中包括有过去颁奖典礼的片断，还有像“{{lang|en|Expected the unexpected}}”（意为“期待惊喜”）和“{{lang|en|It's Oscar night}}”（意为“奥斯卡之夜”）之类口号不时在镜头上闪过<ref name="Pond">{{citation |last=Pond |first=Steve |title=The Big Show: High Times and Dirty Dealings Backstage at the Academy Awards |year=2005 |isbn=0-571-21193-3 |location=New York, United States |edition= |OCLC= |publisher=Faber and Faber}}</ref>{{rp|357}}。这些宣传广告在电影院和多个[[有线电视|有线电视]]频道播映，还有在{{lang|en|[[Blockbuster|Blockbuster]]}}商店销售<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|356}}。学院还史无前例地允许谈话节目主持人奥普拉·温弗里进行采访，接触节目排练，这也是她覆盖了电视转播幕后准备工作的长达一个月[[奥普拉·温弗里秀|同名谈话节目]]的一部分<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|356}}。

=== 美国电影协会的禁令 ===
2003年9月，[[美国电影协会|美国电影协会]]由于担心[[盗版|盗版]]活动而禁止将小成本电影筛选分发给电影奖项评选团体<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|358}}。许多独立电影制片公司和知名导演反对这一做法，因为小成本电影如果要引起学院成员的注意，这一筛选至关重要，所以禁令将对这些电影在奥斯卡奖上斩露头角的机会造成不利影响<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|358}}。次月，美国电影艺术与科学学院和美国电影协会达成一项协议，学院成员将获得筛选电影名单，但他们不能把这些电影泄露给外界人士<ref>{{cite news |last=Friedman |first=Roger |title=TV's 'Ed' Won't Sing for Charity |url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2003/10/22/tv-ed-wont-sing-for-charity/ |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=''Fox News'' |publisher=21st Century Fox |date=2003-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011130245/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2003/10/22/tv-ed-wont-sing-for-charity/ |archive-date=2013-10-11 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。2003年12月，[[纽约|纽约]]一位联邦法官以违反[[反托拉斯法|联邦反托拉斯法]]为由推翻了这道禁令<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|359}}<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2013-10-11 |archivedate=2011-08-30 |deadurl=no |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/12/09/movies/while-they-can-studios-rush-to-send-videos-to-oscar-voters.html |title=While They Can, Studios Rush to Send Videos to Oscar Voters |last=Waxman |first=Sharon |work=The New York Times |publisher=The New York Times Company |date=2003-12-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110830173437/http://www.nytimes.com/2003/12/09/movies/while-they-can-studios-rush-to-send-videos-to-oscar-voters.html }}</ref>。

=== 最佳影片提名作品票房表现 ===
截止1月27日提名名单公布时，所有五部获最佳影片提名的电影[[美国本土|美国本土]]总[[票房|票房]]成绩为6.38亿美元，平均每部1.27亿美元<ref name="BoxOfficeOscars">{{cite news|title=2003 Academy Award Nominations and Winner for Best Picture |url=http://boxofficemojo.com/oscar/chart/?view=&yr=2003&p=.htm |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=''Box Office Mojo'' |publisher=Amazon.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130515042513/http://boxofficemojo.com/oscar/chart/?view=&yr=2003&p=.htm |archivedate=2013-05-15 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。其中《指环王：王者归来》以3亿3834万5008[[美元|美元]]名列榜首，其后分别是收入1亿2023万1534美元的《奔腾年代》，8532万7367美元的《怒海爭鋒：極地征伐》，5911万4051美元的《-{zh:神秘河流;zh-hans:神秘河流;zh-hant:神秘河流;zh-hk:懸河殺機;zh-mo:懸河殺機;zh-tw:神秘河流;}-》和3483万9137美元的《迷失东京》<ref name="BoxOfficeOscars" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Box office totals for some Oscar nominees |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/movieawards/oscars/2004-01-27-lotr-box-office-totals_x.htm |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=USA Today |publisher=Gannett Company |date=2004-01-27 |archive-date=2013-10-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015005526/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/movieawards/oscars/2004-01-27-lotr-box-office-totals_x.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 延时直播 ===
由于[[第三十八届超级碗|第三十八届超级碗]]半场表演时出现的争议性事件影响，[[美国广播公司|美国广播公司]]对直播的节目采取5秒钟的延时，确保不会有粗俗内容直播出去<ref>{{cite news|last=Carey |first=Matt |title=ABC to impose delay on Oscar telecast |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2004/SHOWBIZ/Movies/02/05/sprj.aa04.abc.oscar.delay/ |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=''CNN'' |publisher=Time Warner |date=2004-02-05 |archivedate=2005-01-15 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050115001941/http://edition.cnn.com/2004/SHOWBIZ/Movies/02/05/sprj.aa04.abc.oscar.delay/ }}</ref>。美国电影艺术与科学学院主席弗兰克·皮尔森在一份书面声明中对这一做法表示抗议，认为即使是非政府主导的这种很短暂的延迟也意味着对广播节目进行[[审查制度|审查]]，因为这可能导致电视台对节目进行自我审查以期达到政府的要求，甚至更糟<ref>{{cite news |last=Cadorette |first=Guylaine |title=Academy Miffed about Oscar Tape Delay, Black Eye for the Nerdy Guy, DJ Rick Dees Ends Morning Radio Show, More... |quote=Even a very brief tape-delay introduces a form of censorship into the broadcast{{ndash}}not direct governmental control, but it means that a network representative is in effect guessing at what a government might tolerate, which can be even worse. |url=http://www.hollywood.com/news/brief/1742769/news-feb-11-academy-miffed-about-oscar-tape-delay-black-eye-for-the-nerdy-guy-dj-rick-dees-ends-morning-radio-show-more?page=all |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=Hollywood.com |publisher=Hollywood.com, LLC |date=2004-02-11}}</ref>。对此制片人乔·罗斯表示，只有那些非政治性的亵渎性言辞才会被审查<ref>{{cite news |last=Susman |first=Gary |title=Snippy Response |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20356896_589703,00.html |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=Entertainment Weekly |publisher=Time Warner |date=2004-02-11 |archive-date=2014-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222132814/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0%2C%2C20356896_589703%2C00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 专业评价 ===
颁奖典礼获得的媒体评价褒贬不一。《[[芝加哥論壇報|芝加哥論壇報]]》电视评论员史蒂夫·约翰逊（{{lang|en|Steve Johnson}}）感叹节目“熟悉得几乎让人感到麻木，而且文绉绉得让人失望”。他也批准了美国广播公司延时5秒直播的决定<ref>{{cite news |last=Johnson |first=Steve |title=Crystal's no ball in tepid Oscar show |quote=felt almost numbingly familiar and disappointingly genteel. |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2004-03-01/features/0403010015_1_oscars-new-tune-academy-awards |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=Chicago Tribune |publisher=Tribune Comapny |date=2004-03-01 |archive-date=2015-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411031637/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2004-03-01/features/0403010015_1_oscars-new-tune-academy-awards |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》的{{link-en|汤姆·谢尔斯|Tom Shales}}笑称颁奖典礼的娱乐性和看果冻凝结差不多。他还批评晚会气氛沉闷，缺乏惊喜<ref>{{cite news |last=Shales |first=Tom |title=A Clean and Boring Sweep |quote=was about as entertaining as watching Jell-O congeal. |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A18433-2004Mar1.html |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=The Washington Post |publisher=The Washington Post Company |date=2004-03-01 |archive-date=2015-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413073703/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A18433-2004Mar1.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[旧金山纪事报|旧金山纪事报]]》专栏作家蒂姆·古德曼（{{lang|en|Tim Goodman}}）感叹道：“第76届奥斯卡颁奖典礼上没多少戏剧性和喜剧，虽然表彰的是《指环王》这样的杰作，但还是毫无生命力。”<ref>{{cite news |last=Goodman |first=Tim |title=Unlike 'Lord of the Rings,' this year's Oscars were a yawner - with good ads |quote=The 76th annual Academy Awards dragged on without much drama or comedy, sucking the life out of the event even while it was doing justice to the masterpiece that is ''The Lord of the Rings''. |url=http://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/article/Unlike-Lord-of-the-Rings-this-year-s-Oscars-2815989.php#page-1 |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=San Francisco Chronicle |publisher=Hearst Corporation |date=2004-03-01 |archive-date=2015-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411113047/http://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/article/Unlike-Lord-of-the-Rings-this-year-s-Oscars-2815989.php#page-1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

其它媒体对节目的评价更为正面。《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》的{{link-en|肯·塔克|Ken Tucker}}赞扬了克里斯托的主持，称他在“[[史提夫·馬丁|史提夫·馬丁]]机敏的愚蠢行径和[[琥碧·戈柏|琥碧·戈柏]]毫不悔改的闹剧之间找到了完美的平衡”。而对晚会本身，他认为节目说服了观众2003年是电影业成功的一年，而这一点可能是好莱坞并没有做到的<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,597949,00.html |title=The Show |date=2004-03-12 |first=Ken |last=Tucker |work=Entertainment Weekly |publisher=Time Warner |accessdate=2013-10-11 |quote=managed to do what Hollywood may not have: convince us that this was a great year for the movies. |archive-date=2013-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011134619/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0%2C%2C597949%2C00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[纽约观察家报|纽约观察家报]]》影评人[[安德鲁·萨里斯|安德鲁·萨里斯]]称颁奖典礼是“记忆中最有趣而且最不乏味的”一届。他还对制片人乔·罗斯有高度评价：“从（我）这么一位老评论员来看，罗斯先生，你的工作做得很好。”<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|384}}《[[今日美國|今日美國]]》评论员罗伯特·比安科（{{lang|en|Robert Bianco}}）认为，虽然《指环王》横扫大部分奖项导致晚会缺乏惊喜，但主持人克里斯托还是能够给这个夜晚带来欢笑。他还进一步称赞节目与去年相比更有魅力，更正能量，节奏上更为得体<ref>{{cite news |last=Bianco |first=Robert |title=Crystal's return enlivens predictable show |quote=more glamorous and upbeat than last year's war-muted event, and decently paced. |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/movieawards/oscars/2004-03-01-bianco-review_x.htm |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=USA Today |publisher=Gannett Company |date=2004-03-01 |archive-date=2014-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228202936/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/movieawards/oscars/2004-03-01-bianco-review_x.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 收视和奖项 ===
本次颁奖典礼由美国广播公司在美国直播，其播出时段平均有4356万观众收看，与去年相比提高了26%，而所有观看过部分时段节目的观众总数量则估计有7389万<ref name="rating">{{cite web |first=Bill |last=Gorman |title=Academy Awards Averages 41.3 Million Viewers; Most Since 2005 |url=http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/03/08/academy-awards-averages-41-3-million-viewers-most-since-2005/44217 |work=''TV by the Numbers'' |publisher=Tribune Company |date=2010-03-08 |accessdate=2013-10-11 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130114121751/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2010/03/08/academy-awards-averages-41-3-million-viewers-most-since-2005/44217/ |archivedate=2013-01-14 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Zurawik |first=David |title=Oscars sweep up more viewers |archivedate=2013-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005013853/http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2004-03-02/features/0403020284_1_telecast-viewers-oscar |url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2004-03-02/features/0403020284_1_telecast-viewers-oscar |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=The Baltimore Sun |publisher=Tribune Company |date=2004-03-02 }}</ref>。从尼尔森收视率调查的数量看，节目的表现也强过去年，吸引了26%的[[家庭|家庭]]观看，提升幅度超过27%<ref name="TVB Oscars">{{cite news|title=Academy Awards ratings |work=''Television Bureau of Advertising'' |format=[[PDF|PDF]] |archivedate=2013-09-27 |deadurl=yes |url=http://www.tvb.org/media/file/Academy_Awards.pdf |accessdate=2013-10-11 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927155318/http://www.tvb.org/media/file/Academy_Awards.pdf }}</ref>。此外，节目还在18-49岁年龄段人群中获得了15.3的收视率<ref name="TVB Oscars" />。这也是继2000年的[[第72届奥斯卡颁奖典礼|第72届奥斯卡颁奖典礼]]以来收视成绩最好的一次<ref>{{cite news|last=McDaniel |first=Mike |title=Significant ratings rise for Oscars |url=http://www.chron.com/entertainment/article/Significant-ratings-rise-for-Oscars-1961268.php |date=2004-03-02 |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=Houston Chronicle |publisher=Hearst Corporation |archivedate=2013-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005004535/http://www.chron.com/entertainment/article/Significant-ratings-rise-for-Oscars-1961268.php }}</ref>。

2004年7月，颁奖典礼获得了第56届[[黄金时段艾美奖|黄金时段艾美奖]]的9项提名<ref>{{cite news|title=Primetime Emmy Award database |url=http://www.emmys.com/shows/76th-annual-academy-awards |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=''Academy of Television Arts and Sciences'' |publisher=ATAS |archivedate=2013-06-22 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622210234/http://www.emmys.com/shows/76th-annual-academy-awards }}</ref>，并在两个月后成功为路易斯·J·霍维茨拿下了电视转播指导奖<ref>{{cite news |title=The complete list of winners |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2004/sep/20/entertainment/et-emmylist20 |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=Los Angeles Times |publisher=Tribune Company |date=2004-09-20 |archive-date=2013-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011141213/http://articles.latimes.com/2004/sep/20/entertainment/et-emmylist20 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=2004 Emmy Winners |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/20/arts/television/20emmylist.html?_r=0 |accessdate=2013-10-11 |work=The New York Times |publisher=The New York Times Company |date=2004-09-20 |archive-date=2015-06-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610235809/http://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/20/arts/television/20emmylist.html?_r=0 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 纪念 ==
奥斯卡颁奖典礼上一年一度的“纪念”致敬环节旨在纪念过去一年中逝世的业内人士，本场晚会上的这一环节由学院主席弗兰克·皮尔森引出。蒙太奇中包括了1940年电影《{{link-en|巴格达大盗|The Thief of Baghdad (1940 film)}}》中[[罗饶·米克罗斯|罗饶·米克罗斯]]作曲的“{{lang|en|The Love of the Princess}}”（意为《公主的爱》），他还为《賓漢》、《[[意亂情迷|意亂情迷]]》、《{{link-en|暴君焚城录|Quo Vadis (1951 film)}}》、《[[万王之王|万王之王]]》和《{{link-en|万世英雄|El Cid (film)}}》等电影谱写过配乐：<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|379}}

